    "If L/K is a finite Galois extension, then the Galois group G has two filtrations; the lower-numbering filtration (G u) u∈R and the upper-numbering filtration (G v) v∈R.",
    "These are related by the Herbrand function φ L/K defined by",
    "and its inverse ψ L/K in such a way that",
    "and, if further H is normal, then",
    "Using this property, one can define the upper-numbering filtration (G v) v∈R for an arbitrary (not necessarily finite) Galois extension L/K by defining G v to be the projective limit of Gal(L ′ /K) v, where L ′ /K runs over all finite Galois subextensions of L/K."
